I need to identify the line items and values representing interest accrued but not yet received from the balance sheet.

Looking at the balance sheet, the line item that typically represents interest accrued but not yet received is "Interest Receivable". This account shows money that has been earned as interest but has not yet been received in cash.

From the balance sheet provided:
- The initial value of Interest Receivable as of 2023-12-31 is 0.00
- The end value of Interest Receivable as of 2024-02-03 is 5264.70

These values represent the amounts of interest that have been accrued but not yet received at the beginning and end of the reporting period.

```json
{"solution": {'initial value': '0.00', 'end value': '5264.70'}}
```
